Data Cleaning:

#Remove outliers for micornutrients and crp 
data$sf_outlier<-ifelse(data$sf > (mean(data$sf) + 3*sd(data$sf)) |  data$sf < (mean(data$sf) - 3*sd(data$sf)), 1, 0 )
table(data$sf_outlier) #9 outliers
## 
##   0   1 
## 471   9
data$si_outlier<-ifelse(data$si > (mean(data$si) + 3*sd(data$si)) |  data$si < (mean(data$si) - 3*sd(data$si)), 1, 0 )
table(data$si_outlier) #7 outliers
## 
##   0   1 
## 473   7
data$sfo_outlier<-ifelse(data$sfo > (mean(data$sfo) + 3*sd(data$sfo)) |  data$sfo < (mean(data$sfo) - 3*sd(data$sfo)), 1, 0 )
table(data$sfo_outlier) #9 outliers
## 
##   0   1 
## 471   9
data$vitb12_outlier<-ifelse(data$vitb12 > (mean(data$vitb12) + 3*sd(data$vitb12)) |  data$vitb12 < (mean(data$vitb12) - 3*sd(data$vitb12)), 1, 0 )
table(data$vitb12_outlier) #2 outliers

##   0   1

table(data$crp_outlier) #7 outliers

AIM 1

#Serum ferritin
serum_ferritin1<-lm(sf ~ crp, data = data) #base model, only exposure
serum_ferritin2<-lm(sf ~ crp + age_yr, data = data) #add maternal age only
serum_ferritin3<-lm(sf ~ crp + gagewks, data = data) #add gestational age only
serum_ferritin4<-lm(sf ~ crp + age_yr + gagewks, data = data) #combined model
serum_ferritin5<-lm(sf ~ crp + age_yr + gagewks + crp*gagewks, data = data) #combined model w/ gagewks interaction
serum_ferritin6<-lm(sf ~ crp + age_yr + gagewks + crp*age_yr, data = data) #combined model w/ age_yr interaction

anova(serum_ferritin2, serum_ferritin1) #model 2 better

vitaminb2<-lm(vitb12 ~ crp + age_yr, data = data) #add maternal age only
vitaminb3<-lm(vitb12 ~ crp + gagewks, data = data) #add gestational age only
vitaminb4<-lm(vitb12 ~ crp + gagewks + crp*gagewks, data = data) #combined model w/interaction

anova(vitaminb2, vitaminb1) #model 1 better -> do not include age_yr

full<-glm(as.factor(anemia) ~ sf + sfo + si + vitb12 + crp + age_yr + bmi + gagewks + as.factor(mstatus) + as.factor(trimester) + as.factor(tpreg) +
            sf*age_yr + sfo*age_yr + si*age_yr + vitb12*age_yr + crp*age_yr + 
            sf*bmi + sfo*bmi + si*bmi + vitb12*bmi + crp*bmi + 
            sf*gagewks + sfo*gagewks + si*gagewks + vitb12*gagewks + crp*gagewks +
            sf*as.factor(mstatus) + sfo*as.factor(mstatus) + si*as.factor(mstatus) + vitb12*as.factor(mstatus) + crp*as.factor(mstatus) +
            sf*as.factor(trimester) + sfo*as.factor(trimester) + si*as.factor(trimester) + vitb12*as.factor(trimester) + crp*as.factor(trimester) +
            sf*as.factor(tpreg) + sfo*as.factor(tpreg) + si*as.factor(tpreg) + vitb12*as.factor(tpreg) + crp*as.factor(tpreg),
          family = binomial(link = "logit"), data)

  full,
  criterion = "bic",
  test = "lr",
  direction="backward")

step.model <- train(anemia ~ sfo + si + gagewks, 
                    data = train_data,
                    family = binomial(link = "logit"),
                    method = "leapSeq", 
                    tuneGrid = data.frame(nvmax = 1:3),
                    trControl = train.control
)
## Warning in train.default(x, y, weights = w, ...): You are trying to do
## regression and your outcome only has two possible values Are you trying to do
## classification? If so, use a 2 level factor as your outcome column.
